## 7. FAQ PAGE COPY

**Headline:** Frequently Asked Questions

**General Questions:**

**Q: How do I know if I’m a good candidate for surgery?**  
A: The best candidates are in good overall health, have realistic expectations, and are seeking improvement rather than perfection. During your consultation we will discuss your goals honestly and determine together whether surgery is the right path.

**Q: Will I look natural after surgery?**  
A: This is our highest priority. We are known for results that enhance rather than alter. Our philosophy is “you, but better.”

**Q: How much does a consultation cost?**  
A: The initial consultation with one of our surgeons is €150. This fee is fully credited toward any procedure you decide to book.

**Q: Do you offer financing?**  
A: Yes. We work with several reputable medical financing partners offering 0% interest plans up to 24 months for qualifying patients.

**Q: Can I see before and after photos of patients similar to me?**  
A: Absolutely. During your consultation we will show you relevant cases (with consent) so you can see realistic outcomes for your body type and age.

**Procedure-Specific Questions (select examples):**

**Q: How long do facelift results last?**  
A: A well-performed deep plane facelift typically lasts 10–15 years. You will continue to age naturally, but you will always look younger than if you had never had the procedure.

**Q: Can I combine multiple procedures?**  
A: Yes. Many patients choose to combine procedures (e.g., facelift + blepharoplasty, or breast augmentation + tummy tuck) to reduce overall recovery time and cost.

**Q: What if I’m not happy with my results?**  
A: We stand behind our work. While no surgeon can guarantee perfection, we offer revision policies and will work with you to address any concerns. Our revision rate is among the lowest in the country.

**Q: How soon can I travel after surgery?**  
A: For international patients, we generally recommend staying in Thessaloniki for 7–14 days depending on the procedure. We provide detailed aftercare instructions and are available for virtual follow-ups.

